author: @sentdex
text: Yep. Once you hit the 2GB mark, your program will grind to a halt and die.  As for installing: If the module was simple enough, it wouldn't matter...ie: if it was just a group of .py files. If it is a python wrapper around a C app, then yeah, you must reinstall for sure. Definitely worth having the 2GB limit lifted though!
